OL,6,F"But today, standing in here and
OL,7,Fwalking into empty room, to empty
OL,8,Froom, where you can actually see that
OL,9,Fyou've got nothing is sobering."
OL,11,FThe house was Katie's childhood home,
OL,12,Fwhich she went on to share with her
OL,13,Fpartner Nathan and their children,
OL,14,FRebecca, 12, who is registered
OL,15,Fpartially sighted, Emily, eight, seven-
OL,16,Fyear-old Harley, who is diagnosed with
OL,17,Fautism, and Freddy who is two-years-
OL,18,Fold.
